DESPITE the ongoing Senzo Meyiwa trial, Kelly Khumalo is back with season three of her reality show. In the trailer of the show, Kelly said: “They hate the fact that I am the one who did not die that day.” This season sees Kelly trending after the release of a Senzo documentary and his trial about to start. She will share her feelings about Senzo’s family, Jub Jub and Brenda Mtambo. She will also be working on her album and her businesses, Controversy Gin and Kelly Khumalo Skin by Bioquantine. Wanda Baloyi, Somizi, Sjava and Dr Hlengiwe Mhlaba will make guest appearances. ALSO READ: Zandie's track Ikhwela causes an uproar! Speaking to Daily Sun, Candice Fangueiro, head of content for Showmax said: “Life With Kelly Khumalo has been extremely popular with fans on Showmax. Season one of Life With Kelly Khumalo launched in August 2020, trended at number one on Twitter and quickly became the then fastest Showmax Original to top one million views. “The series also went on to win the 2021 SAFTA for Best Soap Structured Reality TV Show. So we’re confident that season three is going to be the most talked about edition of the show yet.” The third season is set to launch on 5 July on Showmax, with new episodes every Tuesday.